One of the most striking debut albums ever released, this disc instantly
established Chapman as a musical force, and with good reason. Immediacy,
integrity of purpose, and unqualified artistry are apparent in nearly every
song. And while "Fast Cars" remains Chapman&#039;s best-known work, "Talkin&#039;
Bout a Revolution" is that rarest breed: a song which is both topical and
timeless. Any exploration into Chapman&#039;s work should begin with this at times
stunning effort; it&#039;s a disc of remarkable uniformity and clarity that Chapman
has yet to improve on. --Wayne Pernu
